---
description: Documentation standards for code comments and docstrings
globs: src/**/*.{ts,tsx}
alwaysApply: false
---

Document why, not what. Only add a comment if it conveys information the code itself cannot. Never narrate what the code obviously does.

Do document: purpose, constraints, trade-offs, non-obvious decisions, known debt with pointers to tasks.

Do not document: obvious logic, simple wrappers, self-evident one-liners.

Module/file-level comments: explain what the module owns and any non-obvious limitations.

Function/component comments: only when there are meaningful constraints, failure modes, or side effects beyond what the name and types convey.
